               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>A Tamil version of the <title xml:lang="sa">Rāmāyaṇa</title> in the form of a play (<foreign xml:lang="sa">nāṭaka</foreign>; see U2, f14r4).</p>
<p>The description of BnF Indien 532 and 533 as respectively <title xml:lang="ta">Periyapurāṇam</title> (374 ff., from Haas) and <title xml:lang="ta">Rāmāyaṇam</title> (374 ff., from Haas) in Cabaton (1912) is incorrect and should be reversed. The manuscripts are described in the right order by Feer in Vinson et al. (1866-), but a later hand (in black pencil) corrected and inverted the shelfmarks (correction taken into account by Cabaton, whereas the BnF shelfmark stickers remained unchanged on the manuscript.</p>
<p>Description based on the digital images available on Gallica.</p>
<p>Dimensions after Cabaton (1912, no. 533).</p>         

                    </summary>
                  
